HEADWORD: Witherite
<hw>With"er*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called after
Dr. W. <ets>Withering</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Barium
carbonate occurring in white or gray six-sided twin crystals, and also
in columnar or granular masses.</def>⟦br⟧
